rese Johaug]]\n|\n| <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100311022416/http://www.fis-ski.com/uk/604/610.html?sector=CC&raceid=16216 FIS Cross-Country Skiing World Cup Oslo 13 March 2010 women's 30 km freestyle mass start results.] - accessed 13 March 2010.</ref>\n|- \n| align=center|19\n| align=center|26\n| align=right|14 March 2010 &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Oslo]]\n| align=right|Sprint F &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Bj\u00f8rgen]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Kikkan Randall]]\n| {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Natalya Korostelyova]]\n|\n| <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100322201221/http://www.fis-ski.com/uk/604/610.html?sector=CC&raceid=16219 FIS Cross-Country Skiing World Cup Oslo 14 March 2010 women's sprint freestyle results.] - accessed 14 March 2010.</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=10|\n|-bgcolor=\"#98FB98\"\n| align=center|\n| align=center|27\n| align=right|{{nowrap|17 March 2010}} &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Stockholm]] \n| align=right|{{nowrap|Sprint C}} &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anna Olsson (skier)|Anna Olsson]]\n| {{flagicon|POL}} [[Justyna Kowalczyk]]\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Bj\u00f8rgen]]\n| \n| <ref>[http://www.fis-ski.com/pdf/2010/CC/3200/2010CC3200STC.pdf FIS Cross-Country Skiing World Cup Stockholm 17 March 2010 women's sprint classic results.] - accessed 18 March 2010.</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#98FB98\"\n| align=center|\n| align=center|28\n| align=right|19 March 2010 &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Falun]] \n| align=right|2.5&nbsp;km C &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|POL}} [[Justyna Kowalczyk]]\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Bj\u00f8rgen]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Charlotte Kalla]]\n| \n| <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100314015220/http://www.fis-ski.com/uk/604/610.html?sector=CC&raceid=16226 FIS Cross-Country Skiing World Cup Falun 19 March 2010 women's 2.5 km classic individual results.] - accessed 19 March 2010.</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#98FB98\"\n| align=center|\n| align=center|29\n| align=right|20 March 2010 &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Falun]] \n| align=right|10&nbsp;km Skiathlo